commitResults.messageTitle: Add storage feature, more exceptions for bad storage
commitResults.messageBody:
Yap does not have a storage feature, resulting in all data being loss when program is stopped

Storage feature is necessary as users will want tasks to be saved even when they exit the program

Create such storage feature which saves the task as Task Type | Completion Status | Duration related stuff

Current command class does not verify input before trying to parse it

This will cause an error to be thrown if the user inputs something wrongly

Insert an assert line in every command to verify it is a correct command before parsing

Assertions are a good way to check a variable's state at a current point of the program

commitResults.messageTitle: Update Command and UI to follow SRP
commitResults.messageBody:
The UI and Command prints out the results of the command.
This is not ideal as the GUI would not work properly.

Let's change the methods in these classes to return strings of the
outputs.

This will allow the output to be easily passed to the GUI while
maintaining usability of the Yap chatbot on command line.
